  "texts": [
    "For the cases not specified in Section 4, negative responses could be repeating the previous response, rejecting the request, or, in the case of navigational intents, providing the incorrect step to the user.",
    "To increase response diversity and train the models to control the tone of voice, each dialogue is annotated with a randomly tone of voice label.",
    "This label can be one of the following: 1) neutral, 2) somewhat polite, 3) polite, 4) very polite.",
    "To condition the system responses to follow the target tone of voice, we augment each system response template by creating four versions of it (one for each tone of voice label).",
    "Template-based system responses are then sampled only from the set of responses corresponding to the dialogue label."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}